  "question": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?",
  "prompt": "Carla is downloading a 200 GB file. Normally she can download 2 GB/minute, but 40% of the way through the download, Windows forces a restart to install updates, which takes 20 minutes. Then Carla has to restart the download from the beginning. How load does it take to download the file?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "160",
  "generated_text": "To find the total time Carla takes to download the file, we need to break the process down into three stages:\n1.  **Initial download**: Downloading for 40% of the time before the restart.\n2.  **Restart delay**: The time it takes for Windows to restart.\n3.  **Second download**: Downloading the remaining 60% of the file from the beginning.\n\n**Step 1: Calculate the time for the first download.**\nCarla downloads at a rate of $2 \\text{ GB/min}$.\nThe file size is $200 \\text{ GB}$.\nThe first segment covers $40\\%$ of the file.\n$$ \\text{Time}_1 = 200 \\text{ GB} \\times 0.40 = 80 \\text{ GB} $$\n$$ \\text{Time}_1 = \\frac{80 \\text{ GB}}{2 \\text{ GB/min}} = 40 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Step 2: Calculate the total time after the restart.**\nThe download is paused at $80 \\text{ GB}$.\nWindows restarts for $20 \\text{ minutes}$.\nAfter the restart, she has to download the remaining $60\\%$ of the file.\n$$ \\text{Remaining File Size} = 200 \\text{ GB} \\times 0.60 = 120 \\text{ GB} $$\n$$ \\text{Time}_2 = \\frac{120 \\text{ GB}}{2 \\text{ GB/min}} = 60 \\text{ minutes} $$\n\n**Step 3: Calculate the total time.**\nAdd the initial download time, the restart delay, and the second download time",
